  "title": "Business Development Executive",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a motivated <strong>Business Development Executive</strong> to support the\ngrowth of our manpower contracting and logistics services business. The role\ninvolves identifying new business opportunities, building client relationships,\nand supporting the company’s strategic expansion into manpower and freight\ntransport solutions. This position requires strong analytical, negotiation, and\nbusiness development skills, suitable for an applicant with a background in\ninternational logistics and trade finance.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Identify, develop, and secure new business opportunities in manpower contracting and logistics services.</li><li>Build and maintain strong relationships with clients, including SMEs and large enterprises, to understand their manpower and transport requirements.</li><li>Conduct market research and analysis to identify industry trends, competitor activities, and potential areas for business expansion.</li><li>Prepare business proposals, quotations, and presentations to attract new clients.</li><li>Support contract negotiations and ensure compliance with company policies and relevant regulations.</li><li>Collaborate with internal teams (operations) to ensure seamless service delivery for manpower solutions.</li><li>Track and report sales performance, business pipeline, and market intelligence to management.</li><li>Identify cross-selling opportunities between manpower services and freight\ntransport solutions.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in <strong>International Logistics, Trade Finance, Business\nAdministration, or related field</strong>.</li><li>Strong understanding of manpower contracting and logistics operations.</li><li>Excellent communication, negotiation, and interpersonal skills.</li><li>Analytical mindset with the ability to interpret data and market trends.</li><li>Proactive, self-motivated, and result-driven.</li><li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team.</li></ul>",
